                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Meyer</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy, St. Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-06-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 23, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Meyer states that he has been advised by a responsible party who has just
                    returned from investigating the massacre of the Jews last week that 100 were
                    killed and nearly 100 wounded, that there were several cases of mutilation, but
                    none of ravishing, and that the rioters plundered considerable of the property
                    of the Jews. He adds that evidence points to the work and enmity of the lower
                    local military and police officials, who acted without instructions from St.
                    Petersburg.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
